'''José María Giménez de Vargas''' ({{IPA|es|xoˈse maˈɾi.a xiˈmenes ðe ˈβaɾɣas}};{{efn-lg|In isolation, ''Vargas'' is pronounced {{IPA|es|ˈbaɾɣas|}}.}} born 20 January 1995) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club  [[Atlético Madrid]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

After starting out his professional career with [[Danubio FC]], Giménez signed for [[Atlético Madrid]], where he would spend over a decade and play more than 350 games. He won five major titles with the latter, including the [[La Liga]] title  in [[2013–14 La Liga|2013–14]] and [[2020–21 La Liga|2020–21]], as well as the [[UEFA Europa League]] in [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League|2017–18]].

At international level, Giménez made his Uruguay debut in 2013, and has since represented the nation at three [[FIFA World Cup]]s and five editions of the [[Copa América]].

==Club career==
===Danubio===
Born in [[Toledo, Uruguay|Toledo]], Giménez made his professional debut for [[Danubio F.C.]] in the [[Uruguayan Primera División]] on 17 November 2012 (when the manager was [[Juan Ramón Carrasco]]) against [[Club Atlético River Plate (Montevideo)|River Plate]] in which he started and played the full 90 minutes as Danubio lost the match 2–0.<ref>{{cite web|title=DANUBIO VS. RIVER PLATE 0 - 2|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/11/17/uruguay/primera-division/danubio-futbol-club/ca-river-plate/1380964/|work=Soccerway|access-date=27 April 2013}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
====2013–2016====
On 24 April 2013, it was confirmed that Giménez had signed on a five-year deal with Spanish side [[Atlético Madrid]], and would join the club in the pre-season of the [[2013–14 La Liga|2013–14 season]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Casáñez |first1=Juan |title=El Atlético ficha a Giménez, defensa uruguayo de Danubio|trans-title=Atlético sign Giménez, Uruguayan Danubio defender|url=https://as.com/futbol/2013/04/24/mas_futbol/1366831987_577353.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Diario AS |date=24 April 2013 |language=Spanish}}</ref> On 14 September, Giménez made his ''Atleti'' – and [[La Liga]] – debut, starting in a 4–2 home win over [[UD Almería]].<ref>[http://espnfc.com/en/report/373177/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=3888 Atleti maintain perfect start] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023103025/http://espnfc.com/en/report/373177/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=3888 |date=23 October 2013 }}; [[ESPN FC]], 14 September 2013</ref> It was his only appearance of a league-winning season.<ref name=goles>{{cite news |title=Todos los goles y títulos de Josema Giménez con Atlético de Madrid |trans-title=All of Josema Giménez's goals and titles with Atlético Madrid|url=https://www.espn.com.ar/futbol/espana/nota/_/id/11950955/josema-gimenez-goles-titulos-atletico-de-madrid |access-date=25 December 2025 |publisher=ESPN |date=24 April 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.co.za/Soccer/International/Atletico-Madrid-win-La-Liga-20140517|title=Atletico Madrid win La Liga|publisher=Sport 24|date=17 May 2014|access-date=29 January 2015}}</ref> Giménez's appearances were initially limited by competition from compatriot [[Diego Godín]], as well as [[Miranda (footballer, born 1984)|Miranda]] and [[Toby Alderweireld]].<ref>{{cite news |title=La trayectoria de Josema Giménez en Atlético de Madrid |url=https://www.espn.com.gt/futbol/espana/nota/_/id/11950750/josema-gimenez-trayectoria-atletico-de-madrid |access-date=25 December 2025 |publisher=ESPN |date=24 April 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

In August 2014, Giménez won the [[Supercopa de España]] against [[Madrid derby|rivals]] [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], though he did not leave the substitutes' bench in either game.<ref name=goles/> He scored his first goal for the club on 6 December 2014, opening a 2–0 win away to [[Elche CF]] to move Atlético into second place.<ref>{{cite news|title=Elche 0-2 Atl Madrid|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30330862|access-date=6 December 2014|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=6 December 2014}}</ref> He played more often in [[2014–15 Atlético Madrid season|2014–15]] due to Alderweireld's departure,<ref name=dual/> and the club then sold Miranda to [[Inter Milan]], with Giménez having achieved higher averages per game of tackles and interceptions than the Brazilian veteran.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Walker |first1=Joseph |title=Selling Miranda makes sense for Atletico Madrid |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37424921/selling-joao-miranda-makes-sense-atletico-madrid |access-date=25 December 2025 |publisher=ESPN |date=20 June 2015}}</ref> Giménez was a regular starter the [[2015–16 Atlético Madrid season|following season]], until losing his place to [[Stefan Savić]] for the last third of the campaign.<ref name=dual>{{cite news |last1=Pettigrove |first1=Jason |title=Gimenez gets dual nationality |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2016/07/10/57821f9b268e3e36798b45a2.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Marca |date=10 July 2016}}</ref>

====2016–2019====
[[File:Loko-AM2018 (2).jpg|thumb|left|Giménez with Atlético in 2018]]
In July 2016, Giménez was naturalised as a citizen of Spain, thereby freeing up one of Atlético's three spots for players from outside the European Union.<ref name=dual/> He struggled for appearances in [[2016–17 Atlético Madrid season|2016–17]], due to injuries and the form of Godín, Savić and [[Lucas Hernandez]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Barbero |first1=Alberto R. |title=Gimenez to fight for place at Atletico |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2016/11/08/5821883bca4741ad318b45d2.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Marca |date=8 November 2016}}</ref> On 27 September 2017, he made his 100th appearance in a Champions League group 2–1 home loss to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], and was honoured with a plaque on the "Walk of Legends" at Atlético's new [[Metropolitano Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Giménez colocó su placa en el ‘Paseo de Leyendas’|trans-title=Giménez placed his plaque on the 'Walk of Legends' |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20171013/432029599197/jose-maria-gimenez-coloco-placa-paseo-leyendas-atletico-madrid.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Mundo Deportivo |date=14 October 2017 |language=Spanish}}</ref> His team won the [[UEFA Europa League]], with him partnering Godín in central defence for the 3–0 win over [[Olympique de Marseille]] in the [[2018 UEFA Europa League final|final]] on 16 May.<ref>{{cite news |title=Godín y Josema campeones de la Europa League con el Atlético Madrid|trans-title=Godín and Josema champions of the Europa League with Atlético Madrid|url=https://www.subrayado.com.uy/godin-y-josema-campeones-la-europa-league-el-atletico-madrid-n504229 |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Subrayado |date=16 May 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

In June 2018, with 134 games to his name, Giménez signed a new five-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=José María Giménez renueva con el Atlético de Madrid por cinco temporadas más|trans-title=José María Giménez renews with Atlético Madrid for five more seasons |url=https://www.elmundo.es/deportes/futbol/2018/06/13/5b215d3ce5fdeac8558b457c.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=El Mundo |date=13 June 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref> Atlético won the [[2018 UEFA Super Cup]] on 15 August, with Giménez playing as a substitute for [[Diego Costa]] in the last 10 minutes of extra time in a 4–2 win over Real Madrid in [[Tallinn]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Murray |first1=Scott |title=Real Madrid 2-4 Atlético Madrid (aet; 2-2 after 90 mins): Uefa Super Cup – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/aug/15/real-madrid-v-atletico-madrid-uefa-super-cup-live |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=The Guardian |date=15 August 2018}}</ref> On 20 February 2019, he scored the opener in 2-0 home win against Italian champions [[Juventus]] to give Atlético the advantage in the first leg of the [[2018-19 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Round of 16]] fixture in the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Giménez and Godín put Atlético Madrid in charge against Juventus|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/feb/20/atletico-madrid-juventus-champions-league-match-report|date=20 February 2019|work=The Guardian}}</ref>

====2019–====
Ahead of the [[2019–20 Atlético Madrid season|2019–20 season]], after Godín's departure, manager [[Diego Simeone]] named [[Koke (footballer, born 1992)|Koke]] as Atlético [[Captain (association football)|captain]], followed by [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] [[Jan Oblak]], then Giménez as third-captain.<ref>{{cite news |title=Giménez: "Es un orgullo ser uno de los capitanes de Atlético Madrid"|trans-title=Giménez: "It's a pride to be one of the captains of Atlético Madrid" |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/6175520/gimenez-es-un-orgullo-ser-uno-de-los-capitanes-de-atletico-madrid |access-date=25 December 2025 |publisher=ESPN |date=9 October 2019}}</ref> Atlético won the league in [[2020–21 La Liga|2020–21]], with Simeone, Giménez and Koke the only veterans of their previous triumph in 2014; Savić and [[Mario Hermoso]] were the preferred central defensive pairing.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lowe |first1=Sid |title=Atlético Madrid win it the hard way to live up to Diego Simeone’s prediction |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2021/may/24/atletico-madrid-win-la-liga-hard-way-diego-simeone-prediction |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=The Guardian |date=24 May 2021}}</ref>

In August 2021, on 216 appearances across all competitions, Giménez's contract was extended to 2025.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gómara |first1=Javier G. |title=Giménez renueva con el Atlético hasta 2025|trans-title=Giménez renews with Atlético until 2025|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20210812/1001675384/gimenez-renueva-atletico-2025.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Mundo Deportivo |date=12 August 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref> On 6 August 2023, this was extended to 2028.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Medina |first1=David G. |title=Giménez renueva hasta 2028|trans-title=Giménez renews until 2028 |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/atletico/2023/10/06/65203a0b22601dc4348b4582.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Marca |date=6 October 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He made his 300th appearance for the club on 16 December that year, coming on as a substitute for [[Çağlar Söyüncü]] in a 2–0 loss at [[Athletic Bilbao]]; he became the 31st player to reach the mark.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zimmermann |first1=Walter |title=Giménez jugó su partido 300 saliendo desde el banquillo|trans-title=Giménez played his 300th game by coming off the bench |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20231216/1002155059/gimenez-jugo-partido-300-saliendo-banquillo.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=Mundo Deportivo |date=16 December 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Go_Uruguay!_-_Arriba_Uruguay!_-_140619-6398-jikatu_(14307280607).jpg|thumb|Giménez (upper row, second from the right) lining up for a team photo during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Giménez participated for [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]] at the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] as the team finished as runner-up to [[France national under-20 football team|France]].<ref name=fifa>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/players/player=368655/profile-detail.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140911131829/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/players/player=368655/profile-detail.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=11 September 2014|title=Jose GIMENEZ|access-date=22 June 2014|work=FIFA.com}}</ref>

He debuted for the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay senior team]] in a [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] on 10 September 2013.<ref name=fifa/>

On 2 June 2014, Giménez was named in Uruguay's squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] finals.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/uruguay/10810104/Uruguay-World-Cup-2014-squad.html|title=Uruguay World Cup 2014 squad|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=2 June 2014|access-date=18 June 2014}}</ref> The 19-year-old defender made his tournament debut against [[England national football team|England]] in the team's second group match, deputising for the injured captain [[Diego Lugano]] in a 2–1 victory for ''La Celeste''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Mondiali/21-06-2014/mondiali-uruguay-lugano-ancora-out-contro-italia-ritocca-baby-gimenez-80999714413.shtml|title=Mondiali, Uruguay, Lugano ancora out: contro l'Italia (ri)tocca a baby Gimenez|trans-title=World Cup, Uruguay, Lugano still out: against Italy they will turn to baby Gimenez|language=it|date=21 June 2014|access-date=22 June 2014|work=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]}}</ref> He went on to start in the final group match – a 1–0 win over [[Italy national football team|Italy]] – and the 2–0 [[2014 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] loss to [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=368655/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130619080516/http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=368655/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=19 June 2013|title=José María Giménez|access-date=13 June 2015|work=FIFA}}</ref>

Giménez scored his first international goal in a 1–0 friendly win against [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] on 8 September 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espnfc.com.au/blog/espn-fc-united-blog/68/post/2142706/tim-vickery-four-up-and-coming-prospects-from-brazil-bolivia-peru-and-uruguay|title=Stakes are high in South American friendlies as players look to impress|date=12 November 2014|work=ESPN}}</ref> In May 2015, he was named in [[2015 Copa América squads#Uruguay|Uruguay's squad]] for the [[2015 Copa América]] by coach [[Óscar Tabárez]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Uruguay confirm Copa América squad numbers as Rolán lands Suárez's No.9 |url=http://www.ca2015.com/en/news/uruguay-confirm-copa-america-squad-numbers-with-rolan-taking-suarezs-no9/1g4mw7am9khxi1dcpc7jxfh8f4 |access-date=9 June 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612033334/http://www.ca2015.com/en/news/uruguay-confirm-copa-america-squad-numbers-with-rolan-taking-suarezs-no9/1g4mw7am9khxi1dcpc7jxfh8f4 |archive-date=12 June 2015 }}</ref> On 20 June, he scored Uruguay's goal in a 1–1 draw with [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] which saw both teams progress to the [[2015 Copa América knockout stage|knockout stage]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/33085636|title=Uruguay 1-1 Paraguay|date=20 June 2015|work=BBC}}</ref>

In May 2018 he was named in Uruguay's provisional 26-man [[Uruguay national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldsoccer.com/world-cup/uruguay-world-cup-fixtures-399702 |title=Uruguay World Cup Fixtures, Squad, Group, Guide |publisher=World Soccer |first1 =Sam |last1=Tremlett |date=15 June 2018 |access-date=15 June 2018 }}</ref> On 15 June, with the score tied at 0–0, he scored the winning goal in the final minute of Uruguay's opening game of the World Cup against [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Emons |first1=Michael |title=Egypt 1–0 Uruguay |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44408321 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=15 June 2018 |date=15 June 2018}}</ref>

In March 2019, Tabárez included Giménez in the final 23-man Uruguay squad for the [[2019 Copa América]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://copaamerica2019.live/uruguay-team-squads/ |title=Uruguay Team Squads Copa America 2019 |work=copaamerica2019.live |date=7 March 2019 |access-date=13 June 2019 |archive-date=16 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416112817/https://copaamerica2019.live/uruguay-team-squads/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> He headed the equaliser in the 2–2 group draw with [[Japan national football team|Japan]] in [[Porto Alegre]],<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Gimenez Header Helps Uruguay Draw Japan in Copa America |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2019/06/21/jose-gimenez-header-sees-uruguay-draw-japan-copa-america |access-date=21 June 2020 |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |date=20 June 2019}}</ref> and was the only Uruguayan in the Team of the Tournament despite a quarter-final exit.<ref name=team/>

On 31 May 2026, Giménez was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Giménez married Regina Iafolla in a civil ceremony in June 2019, prior the Copa América.<ref>{{cite news |title=El casamiento de Josema Giménez y Regina Iafolla|trans-title=Josema Giménez and Regina Iafolla's wedding|url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/tvshow/personajes/el-casamiento-de-josema-gimenez-y-regina-iafolla |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=El País (Uruguay) |date=10 June 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref> They have three sons.<ref>{{cite news |title=José María Giménez y su esposa, Regina Iafolla, celebraron el nacimiento de Santi|trans-title=José María Giménez and his wife, Regina Iafolla, celebrated the birth of Santi |url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Jose-Maria-Gimenez-y-su-esposa-Regina-Iafolla-celebraron-el-nacimiento-de-Santi-uc878040 |access-date=25 December 2025 |publisher=Montevideo Portal |date=29 January 2024 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

